                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5857: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from"
                        >Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-03T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 3, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 3—4:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Military Attaché reports as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“This office estimates by February 15th Japanese regular troops on Asian
                            mainland as follows: Manchuria 70,000 including 30,000 new levy, Korea
                            at least 20,000, North China at least 2,400, total at least 92,000.
                            Further estimate force now available for operation in Jehol and vicinity
                            at least 6 mixed infantry brigades and 2 cavalry brigades, about 21,000,
                            and if necessary this force can be doubled by March 1st from Asia
                            mainland alone.</p>
                        <p>Information here indicates no immediate Japanese movement in force into
                            Jehol.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
